[SN]TITLE[SN]
Appeal after two people seriously hurt in Wrexham crash

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Two people have been seriously injured following a two-car crash in Wrexham.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Emergency services were called to Heritage Way in the Tanyfron area at about 21:45 GMT on Friday evening.
A passenger in a black Ford Fiesta was transferred to hospital in Stoke in a critical condition.
The driver of the car remains in Wrexham's Maelor Hospital with serious injuries. The driver of a blue Audi vehicle suffered minor injuries in the incident.
North Wales Police has appealed for any witnesses to the crash or who saw the vehicles prior to the collision to contact the force.
